{"questionId":"22210162","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>≈</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;in the expansion&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>16</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for at least one correct.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to multiply their two expansions together&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>19</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>≈</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22210162","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.12c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, show that 1-2x-121-4x-12≈2+6x+19x22.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}